UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1435
1 AN ACT proposing to amend Section 1 of the Constitution of Kentucky relating to
2 property exempt from taxation.
3 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
4 Section 1. Are you in favor of providing citizens of the Commonwealth the
5 right to exempt their primary residence and their primary vehicle from property tax after
6 the year 2028 by amending the Constitution of Kentucky to read as stated below?
7 Section 2. It is proposed that Section 1 of the Constitution of Kentucky be
8 amended to read as follows:
9 All men are, by nature, free and equal, and have certain inherent and inalienable
10 rights, among which may be reckoned:
11 First: The right of enjoying and defending their lives and liberties.
12 Second: The right of worshipping Almighty God according to the dictates of their
13 consciences.
14 Third: The right of seeking and pursuing their safety and happiness.
15 Fourth: The right of freely communicating their thoughts and opinions.
16 Fifth: The right of acquiring and protecting property.
17 Sixth: The right of assembling together in a peaceable manner for their common
18 good, and of applying to those invested with the power of government for redress of
19 grievances or other proper purposes, by petition, address or remonstrance.
20 Seventh: The right to bear arms in defense of themselves and of the State, subject to
21 the power of the General Assembly to enact laws to prevent persons from carrying
22 concealed weapons.
23 Eighth: The right of exempting from property tax a property owned and
24 maintained solely as their primary residence and a motor vehicle owned and
25 maintained solely as their primary vehicle after calendar year 2028.
26 Section 3. This amendment shall be submitted to the voters of the
27 Commonwealth for their ratification or rejection at the time and in the manner provided
Page 1 of 2
