UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1435
1 for under Sections 256 and 257 of the Constitution, KRS 118.415, and Sections 4 and 5
2 of this Act.
3 Section 4. Notwithstanding any provision of KRS 118.415 to the contrary, the
4 Secretary of State shall cause the question in Section 1 of this Act and the entirety of the
5 proposed amendment to the Constitution of Kentucky contained in Section 2 of this Act
6 to be published at least one time in a newspaper of general circulation published in this
7 state, and shall also cause to be published at the same time and in the same manner the
8 fact that the amendment will be submitted to the voters for their acceptance or rejection at
9 the next regular election at which members of the General Assembly are to be voted for.
10 The publication required by this section and KRS 118.415 shall be made no later than the
11 first Tuesday in August preceding the election at which the amendment is to be voted on.
12 Section 5. Notwithstanding any provision of KRS 118.415 to the contrary, not
13 later than the second Monday after the second Tuesday in August preceding the next
14 regular election at which members of the General Assembly are to be chosen in a year in
15 which there is not an election for President and Vice President of the United States, or not
16 later than the Thursday after the first Tuesday in September preceding a regular election
17 in a year in which there is an election for President and Vice President of the United
18 States, the Secretary of State shall certify the complete text of Section 1 of this Act and
19 the entirety of the proposed amendment to the Constitution of Kentucky contained in
20 Section 2 of this Act to the county clerk of each county, and the county clerk shall have
21 the entirety of the text and the amendment, as so certified, indicated on the ballots
22 provided to the voters in paper or electronic form as applicable to the voting machines in
23 use in each county or precinct.
